==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Washout
<hw>Wash"out`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
washing out or away of earth, etc., especially of a portion of the bed
of a road or railroad by a fall of rain or a freshet; also, a place,
especially in the bed of a road or railroad, where the earth has been
washed away.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>a complete failure; -- of an enterprise.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>a person who has failed a course of study or
training, leaving the program before its completion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wash out</ent>⟦br⟧
